Aplication Programming Interface 
It is a standerdized format to comunicate two softwares.
It is predefined formate 
our whole internet is defined into servers and clients.
Server is the one who provides the service and client is the one who consumes the service.
EX-Google Maps API, Payment API, etc

REST API: Representational State Transfer API
It is a type of api that use http methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) to communicate.
EX- GET /users, POST /login

api-endpoint: It is the url of the api.
it is the specific place where api listen the requests.
EX- https://api.example.com/orders

API is a communication interface between two software systems.
REST API is a type of API that uses HTTP methods like GET, POST, PUT, DELETE to interact with resources.
An API Endpoint is the URL where the REST API is accessed, like /users, /products, /login.

Endpoint is the specific location where the API receives requests.